WEBVTT

NOTE
Wildfire AF31 Firebreak Simulation — Woodchip and Pine Tree Test
Duration: ~1 minute 24 seconds
Recorded: December 2021

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[Testing area: a bed of woodchips with three small pine trees planted at center]

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:22.000
[Firefighter applies AF31 solution around the perimeter of the woodchip area, creating a firebreak line]

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:35.000
[Fire ignited at the outer edge of the woodchip bed — flames begin spreading through the dry material]

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Aerial and ground camera footage shows flames burning freely through untreated areas]

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:05.000
[Flames reach the AF31 treated perimeter line and stop — fire cannot cross into the treated zone]

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[Fire surrounds the treated central area from all directions but fails to penetrate]

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:24.000
[Central area preserved — three small pine trees and treated woodchips survive the wildfire simulation intact]
